Proposed (12.6s): Use this skill whenever a user has a list of review/audit findings (from /qa-review, /security-review, /ux-review, /ui-polish, /code-review, PR comments, or any multi-finding report) and wants to turn them into GitHub issues plus fix commits on the current branch. Strong triggers: user mentions N findings, Critical/High/Medium/Low severity counts, wants "an issue per finding", wants to fix some and defer/track others, says "remediate", "work through", "apply the review", "address these", or asks to fix findings from a named review report. Creates one issue per finding (including deferred ones for audit trail), asks which to fix this pass, commits atomically with `#N` as first token, closes each issue after push. Stays on current branch — no new branch or PR. Do NOT use for a single ad-hoc bug, new feature work, or anything needing its own branch/PR (use /github-workflow instead), or for simply closing/opening one issue.

