Proposed (12.7s): Use this skill when the user has multiple review/audit/QA findings and wants to both track them as GitHub issues AND fix some (or all) of them with atomic commits on the current branch. Triggers include: user references a review report or named review command (/qa-review, /security-review, /ux-review, /ui-polish, /code-review, PR review comments, parallel review agents, audit reports) and mentions finding counts, severities (Critical/High/Medium/Low, P1/P2), or says things like "remediate", "work through", "apply the review", "address these findings", "fix the Criticals", "issue per finding", "audit trail", or wants to fix some findings now while deferring/tracking the rest. The skill creates one issue per finding (including deferred ones), commits fixes atomically with `#N` as the first token, closes issues after push, and stays on the current branch. Do NOT use for a single standalone bug, new feature work, work needing its own branch/PR (use /github-workflow), or just opening/closing one issue.

